introduction.p:
The equation
                x' = r \left( 1 - \frac{x}{K} \right) x - c \frac{x^2}{a + x^2}
            has been used to describe the dynamics of spruce budworm populations, where the variable x denotes the population or density of the insect.  One explanation that has been given for the occurrence of outbreaks is based on the multiple bifurcations that occur with this differential equation.
